<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Only two specimens are found unter the name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis versicolor" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">Chrysis versicolor</taxonomicName>
in the Spinola collection. One is not a syntype, since it bears a rounded label (6295) and was acquired with other specimens of the Latreille collection. The second specimen is labelled &quot;Type&quot;, and it was collected at Genoa, as written on the main label. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Spinola’s">Spinola's</normalizedToken>
description is surely based on a syntype series (&quot;haud infrequens&quot;), therefore we here designate as lectotype the last syntype left in the collection, even though the specimen is badly damaged. It lacks the metasoma, the right flagellum and almost all of the left flagellum; only the right mesoleg is complete. However, many diagnostic characteristics are still visible and even the sex is identifiable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
